Hey 👋🏼

My name is Jacqueline and I’m currently a computer science student at the University of Waterloo. I’m passionate about software development, learning new things, and bringing people together.

At my previous engineering internships, I’ve helped develop 1100+ microservices to automate accountant and book-keeper tasks using Javascript, HTTP, and networking. I’ve also created websites that have attracted over $50,000 in cancer research funding. Being able to make impact and ultimately help people is what drives my work.

Outside of work, I’m passionate about connecting with people through art, music, and food! I enjoy experimenting with different art mediums, discovering new music, and trying new cuisines. If you’d like to chat with me, please feel free to send a message!
